cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about developing a recurrent neural network for semantic image segmentation that can work across a range of computational budgets. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach to improving prediction quality, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of recurrent neural networks also suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses video segmentation, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
